Mar\E9chal, nous voil\E0 ! (Marshal, here we are!) is a French song dedicated to Marshal Petain. Lyrics were composed by Andr\E9 Montagnard, and music was composed by Andr\E9 Montagnard and Charles Curtioux. The song was performed by Andr\E9 Dassary and whole school children in unoccupied France and Algeria during Vichy France.

La Marseillaise remained the official anthem of the state, but a popular though unofficial patriotic song was Mar\E9chal, nous voil\E0 !. Officially, the song was created in 1940, but Montagnard and Curtioux actually reused another song dedicated to the Tour de France called Voil\E0 le Tour qui passe. The first two lines of that song were:  Attention, les voil\E0 ! les coureurs, les g\E9ants de la route.

